<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="223" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1436,151,360]" pageId="22" pageNumber="223">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,295,320]" pageId="22" pageNumber="223">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name is derived from the Latin, 
<emphasis box="[849,933,297,320]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="223">crassus</emphasis>
(= thick, stout), referring to the more or less thick 3 
<superScript attach="left" box="[228,241,331,345]" fontSize="6" pageId="22" pageNumber="223">rd</superScript>
segment of the labial palpus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
